Attributes (in package)

 Go to Top
Attribute Type Multiplicity Description
details String 0..1 Free text, for notes, explanatory comments, etc.  
isSimulated Boolean 1..1 Are data in this list simulated? The attribute is an annotation more than anything else, as there are no corresponding constraints.  
name Line 0..1 Measurement List name, freely chosen by user. Intended to identify the list from other lists of the same type.  
serial Int 1..1 Serial number of object. Serves as object main key. Serial numbers of deleted objects are not re-used. Serial numbers can only be set by the implementation. Values are in practice always positive, since negative values are interpreted as a signal to set the next free serial  
sf Float 0..1 Spectrometer frequency in MHz at which J couplings were measured.  
unit Word 1..1 Unit of measurement for J couplings - default 'Hz'.
